    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so if mechanical tension is the main driver, does that mean i should just be doing low reps with really heavy weight all the time? or is there a limit to how much tension a muscle can actually handle before it just stops working?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While heavy, low-rep sets excel at maximizing mechanical tension, relying on them exclusively isn't ideal for long-term growth. Muscles can handle significant tension, but incorporating higher-rep work helps induce metabolic stress, providing a different stimulus. Furthermore, progressive overload—consistently increasing the weight or reps over time—is the true driver of continued growth, as muscles adapt to whatever stress is placed upon them.",
      "source": "target",
